title: NACLO 2019 Problem M

title: NACLO 2019 Problem N
notes: Witsuwit'en nominal compounding with transparent semantic composition (24 items); compound words like 'dog harness' = dog + abdomen

title: NACLO 2019 Problem O
notes: Natural language inference (NLI); reverse-engineering spurious patterns learned by neural network from training data; analyzing systematic model errors in semantic entailment task

title: NACLO 2019 Problem P

title: NACLO 2019 Problem Q

title: NACLO 2019 Problem R
notes: Computational linguistics: constraint grammar for POS disambiguation in English and Sranan Tongo (English-based creole from Suriname); requires formal rule-writing
